Telefon AB L M Ericsson &lt;ERIC.ST> saidit would sell its office machinery unit, with a turnover of twobillion crowns, to Norway's &lt;Norska Design Funktion A/S>.    Ericsson Information Systems, of which the unit is a part,said in a statement a decision would be reached in Novemberabout when the Norwegian firm would take over the operation.    No price was given for the deal.    EIS managing director Stig Larsson said the deal wouldallow EIS to concentrate on voice and data communicationproducts. REUTER&#3;